[thinking] **Considering TLS handler behavior**
[thinking] 
[thinking] When dealing with TLS, I'm thinking that the ApplicationProtocolNegotiationHandler removes itself after the negotiation, which may cause it not to trigger channelActive for new handlers. I wonder if handlerAdded actually gets fired instead. It could be that the RootRequestHandler's handlerAdded is called before the Http2FrameCodec's is complete. The way Pipeline.addLast adds components seems orderly, but channel activation needs to defer until pipeline configuration is complete. So, executing the context in a deferred manner might be the solution.
[thinking] 
